    "notes": "Primary detection signal: wmic.exe spawned by non-standard parent (not CcmExec, mmc, or IT tooling) with /node: AND 'process call create' in command_line. Secondary signal: WmiPrvSE.exe spawning cmd.exe or powershell.exe executing a path under AppData or Windows\\Temp. Tune out SCCM (CcmExec.exe parent), monitoring agents, and SYSTEM-context WmiPrvSE children running read-only commands (ipconfig, systeminfo without lateral payload paths). Port 135 egress from unexpected user-context processes is a strong corroborating indicator."
